reset_pll_timing(25.10)                                reset_pll_timing(25.10)

Name
       reset_pll_timing  -  Resets  the delay offset settings applied to a PLL
       (phase locked loop) output clock

Syntax
       reset_pll_timing

       [-help]

       <inst_name>

       -output_clock

       <clock name or ID>

       -output_pin <output pin name>

       Resets the delay offset settings applied to a PLL (phase  locked  loop)
       output clock.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <inst_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  instance on which reference pins,
              feedback pins, or output pins will be searched.

       -output_clock <<clock name or ID>>
              Specifies the name of the PLL output clock.

       -output_pin <<output pin name>>
              Specifies the name of the PLL output pin.

Related Information
              * set_pll_timing

